Foreshadowing is a literary technique used by many different authors to provide clues for the reader to be able to predict what might occur later on in the story. It is a . literary device in which an . author drops hints about the plot and what may come in the near future. It suggests certain plot developments will come later in the story and gives hints about whats going to happen next. Irony is the contrast between what is expected or what appears to be and what
